description:

not set route, no set pace, just a common place to meet up and find company for your monday miles! start the week off right and join us at 6:00pm every first, second, and third monday of the month at the trailhead store! 

what to expect:
- 6:00pm gather & mingle
- 6:05 icebreaker & introductions 
- 6:10pm depart for run
- 7:00pm return to Brooks

there will be a leader there to guide anyone interested in a 4-6 mile route, but you‚Äôre also welcome to buddy up and do your own thing! monday nights are for getting what you need :)

this event is open to women, trans, and non-binary people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that nobody runs alone ‚ù§Ô∏è

*4th/5th monday will typically be field trip runs at outside locations announced on the cowgill strava page
title: womxn run the herd

description:
Werkout with friends!! Come join us for a werkout this Wednesday, January 8th at 6:30am at Greenlake. We are doing the classic 2/2/2 minutes workout around Greenlake. The goal of this workout is to work on changing pace at a harder effort. This is a time/effort based workout meant for all ability levels.

Meetup: Lower Woodland Soccer Parking, 5000 West Green Lake Way N, Seattle, WA 98103

A group will leave for a warmup at 6:30, start drills + strides at 6:50, and werkout starts at 7am

2 min, 8 RPE, threshold effort, ~5k pace
2 min, 7 RPE, steady effort, ~10k-HM effort
2 min, 6 RPE, steady effort, ~marathon pace
Repeat x4-6
20 min cooldown

We should be finished around 8:15

Please RSVP if you plan on joining.
title: Werkout Wednesday
